    <node id="Tea Tray in the Sky&#10; &#10; &#10; By EVELYN E. SMITH&#10; &#10; Illustrated by ASHMAN&#10; &#10; [Transcriber's Note: This etext was produced from Galaxy Science Fiction September 1952. Extensive research did not uncover any evidence that the U.S. copyright on this publication was renewed.]&#10; &#10; &#10; Visiting a society is tougher than being born into it. A 40 credit tour is no substitute!&#10; &#10;&#10; &#10; The picture changed on the illuminated panel that filled the forward end of the shelf on which Michael lay. A haggard blonde woman sprawled apathetically in a chair.&#10; &#10; &quot;Rundown, nervous, hypertensive?&quot; inquired a mellifluous voice. &quot;In need of mental therapy? Buy Grugis juice; it's not expensive. And they swear by it on Meropé.&quot;&#10; &#10; A disembodied pair of hands administered a spoonful of Grugis juice to the woman, whereupon her hair turned bright yellow, makeup bloomed on her face, her clothes grew briefer, and she burst into a fast Callistan clog.&#10; &#10; &quot;I see from your hair that you have been a member of one of the Brotherhood" />
    <node id="1. Michael decided to join the Angeleno Brotherhood because he had been born into it, as his father had brought him when he entered the Brotherhood himself. The exact reason why Michael's father joined the Brotherhood is not mentioned in the story.&#10;2. Michael was impatient to exchange the flowing robes of the Brotherhood for the close-fitting breeches and tunic of the outer world because he found the latter more glamorous when he was young, possibly due to his lack of experience with the outside world. However, after actually experiencing the itchy close-fitting clothes and facing the complexities of the outer world, Michael realized that he preferred the simplicity of the Brotherhood's lifestyle." />
    <node id="1. The reason for the unusual lack of seats and cramped quarters inside the jet bus on Saturn is that the arrangement has proved suitable for the greatest number of intelligent life-forms, as explained by Carpenter. This suggests that the seating arrangements in the jet bus are designed to accommodate a wide variety of extraterrestrial life forms with different physical characteristics and needs.&#10;2. The locals suggest that Michael stick close to them until he learns their ways because they are worried about his ability to adapt to civilized behavior patterns on Talitha and fit in with the local culture and norms. They may also be concerned about Michael's plans to keep his girlfriend exclusively for himself, which goes against the Talithan law promoting shared possession of romantic partners. By sticking close to a guide, Michael can avoid getting into trouble and learn how to navigate the society on Talitha." />
