    <node id="1. Izarians are tiny golden-haired, winged creatures that are in demand for Christmas displays. They were seen over Times Square in July, singing &quot;It Came Upon the Midnight Clear,&quot; which is a well-known Christian hymn and carol associated with the celebration of Christmas. This suggests that these Izarian creatures are used as decorative figures or performers for Christmas displays and events, and their song is likely used to promote the holiday spirit and advertising for Nimble's Christmas gifts.&#10;2. Broadway and boogil trees from Dschubba were mentioned in this context as part of the expository tour that Carpenter was giving to Michael. Boogil trees from Dschubba are a type of tree that provides shade on Broadway, one of the main streets in Times Square. The mention of these trees and the street is meant to give some background information about the location and setting of the story, rather than having any direct relevance to the Izarians or the Christmas displays." />
