    <node id="Based on the story, Portyork's architecture is influenced by its diverse inhabitants from different planets in the United Universe. It is described to have silver domes of Earth crowded next to tall helical edifices of the Venusians. The medieval revival in architecture is also mentioned, with period houses built in the Frank Lloyd Wright and Inigo Jones manner. Additionally, there are great floating red and green balls lighting up the streets, which could be a unique architectural feature of the city or decorations from an extraterrestrial culture. Overall, Portyork's cosmopolitan nature is reflected in its varied and inclusive architecture." />
    <node id="1. The red being reacts with indignation and loathing upon hearing the word &quot;history&quot; because, according to Nekkarian custom, it is forbidden to imply or permit the existence of anything that isn't true. In this case, the concept of history implies the acknowledgment of events or stories from the past, which may no longer be accurate or relevant in the present. By using the word &quot;history,&quot; Michael has inadvertently violated Nekkarian customs regarding truth and reality.&#10;2. This reaction reveals that Nekkar places a strong emphasis on truth and accuracy, to the point where even mentioning the concept of history is considered distasteful. It also suggests that Nekkar's culture and society are focused on the present and future, rather than dwelling on the past. This custom highlights the importance of adapting to local norms and customs when visiting or living in a foreign society, as even seemingly harmless words or concepts can be offensive or misunderstood in different cultural contexts." />
