    <node id="1. Marriage has been outlawed on Talitha because exclusive possession of a member of the opposite sex is considered slavery. This means that according to Talithan law, supposing someone else saw your girlfriend and wanted her, you would not wish him to endure the frustration of not having her. Therefore, if you bring your girl here, you'd have to share her, and she'd have to share you with others if someone wanted you. This policy goes against the traditional Earth concept of marriage where two individuals exclusively commit to each other.&#10;2. The implication of this policy for exclusive possession of a member of the opposite sex is that it is not allowed or recognized on Talitha. Instead, the society promotes shared possession of romantic partners, which is a significant departure from Earth's cultural norms and laws regarding relationships and marriage." />
